ss/webp-images/uploads/2021/06/e42ecd01-f6bc-4ab4-b3a2-9457fce461bb.jpg.webp";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSokTf8Q_Lvy9GovUaD44CzbkA20odHemcFxg";s:8:"filetype";s:4:"webp";s:5:"width";i:1600;s:6:"height";i:1200;s:6:"source";s:74:"https://stigaragedoor.com/how-to-fix-a-bent-garage-door-panel-tips-tricks/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"stigaragedoor.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:57:{i:0;s:98:"When your track is not aligned properly our common garage problems turns into more of a nightmare.";i:1;s:94:"The metal track your door runs on needs to be aligned properly in order for your door to move.";i:2;s:97:"If you see gaps between the rollers and rail or bends in the rails themselves you have a problem.";i:3;s:59:"A garage door thats out of alignment can be very dangerous.";i:4;s:79:"If its way off-balance it could actually fall of the tracks and injure someone.";i:5;s:101:"The door may get jammed and there could be an emergency situation where you need to get your car out.";i:6;s:70:"A door that wont close and lock leaves you vulnerable to burglars too.";i:7;s:123:"If the panels were not moving together I suspect the hinge hardware was coming loose and the panels were no longer aligned.";i:8;s:62:"Especially since you said it was working fine just previously.";i:9;s:64:"Another problem can be the condition and alignment of the rails.";i:10;s:62:"Its not uncommon for these tracks to wind up out of alignment.";i:11;s:55:"This can happen if your garage door receives an impact.";i:12;s:80:"It can also happen as a result of the securing hardware working loose over time.";i:13;s:110:"The problem with a misaligned garage door track is that it can cause problems with the operation of your door.";i:14;s:94:"Adjusting the garage door track margins keeps the track properly aligned with the door itself.";i:15;s:81:"When it is resting on the ground the door establishes where the tracks should be.";i:16;s:110:"You want the tracks to be parallel with the door and have a consistent margin for the full height of the door.";i:17;s:205:"If you think that your garage door is not working properly due to a misaligned garage door sensor you need to check whether the stored item or object is hindering the light beam in-between those two units.";i:18;s:121:"If they are not aligned properly or maintained well they can become noisy jerky or even dangerous if they come off track.";i:19;s:176:"For this reason it is advisable to lubricate your door often with a silicone based lubricant and set up an annual tune up to make sure it is running at its optimal performance.";i:20;s:80:"Adjusting the Tracks for a Binding Garage Door Step 1 - Loosen the Track Screws.";i:21;s:157:"If the garage doors bind or are hard to move up or down in the tracks use a screwdriver to loosen the screws that secure the tracks to the garage door frame.";i:22;s:35:"Step 2 - Adjust the Track Position.";i:23;s:152:"An easy way to tell if your garage door sensors are out of alignment is by checking if the exterior LED light blinks when you attempt to close the door.";i:24;s:96:"Green lights mean the sensors are working while red lights indicate the sensors are not aligned.";i:25;s:74:"If you see red lights try inspecting the bracket or tightening a screw on.";i:26;s:147:"The best way to determine if your garage door is no longer aligned is by noting unusual operations like unpleasant noises or inconsistent movement.";i:27;s:150:"Garage doors can easily become misaligned due to loose damaged hardware or force that causes the panels to become damaged or dislodged from the track.";i:28;s:44:"Doors not aligned - GMC 1986 K2500 question.";i:29;s:99:"Clicking this will make more experts see the question and we will remind you when it gets answered.";i:30;s:161:"Aligned Garage Doors LLC is a garage door repair service and installation company owned and operated by Victor Noyes and Amanda Noyes of Saint Augustine Florida.";i:31;s:91:"Victor Noyes 47 is originally from ups