ut a careless mistake could cause serious injury.";i:53;s:116:"To reduce the risk always have the correct tools safety equipment and knowledge you need before attempting a repair.";i:54;s:110:"The panels themselves can be heavy so although the project can be done solo it is a good idea to recruit some.";i:55;s:24:"Close the door manually.";i:56;s:236:"Relieve the chainbelt tension by loosening both the shaft linker and the flange nut see page 6-7 Operate the opener so the trolley shaft travels towards the door trolley should be kept disconnected Refer to page 16 to decrease UP limit.";}}